content.text:
Let me analyze the target structure and provide assembly instructions:

Analysis of the Main Target Image:
- The structure consists of two connected buildings/sections
- Left section: Red archway with orange cylinders and green supports, topped with orange triangular roof
- Right section: Green pillars with yellow horizontal pieces, red base with arches, topped with orange triangular roof
- Multiple layers and various block types are used including rectangular blocks, cylinders, arches, and triangular roof pieces

Block Selection and Assembly Order:
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1 (red arch base - right side)
    Step2: Move block with index 2 (red arch base - left side)
    Step3: Move block with index 5 (green vertical block - left back)
    Step4: Move block with index 5 (green vertical block - left front)
    Step5: Move block with index 10 (orange cylinder - left back)
    Step6: Move block with index 11 (orange cylinder - left front)
    Step7: Move block with index 12 (orange triangular roof - left side)
    Step8: Move block with index 5 (green vertical block - right back)
    Step9: Move block with index 5 (green vertical block - right front)
    Step10: Move block with index 7 (yellow horizontal block - top)
    Step11: Move block with index 8 (yellow horizontal block - bottom)
    Step12: Move block with index 9 (yellow vertical block - right side)
    Step13: Move block with index 3 (red curved base - right side)
    Step14: Move block with index 4 (red curved piece - connecting piece)
    Step15: Move block with index 12 (orange triangular roof - right side)
}

The structure is built from bottom to top, starting with the base elements and working up to the roof pieces. Some blocks (like index 5 for green vertical blocks) are used multiple times in different positions.
